<body>
<p>After publication, it was determined that several direct quotations from other published work were not properly referenced by the use of inverted commas, as is required by both journal policy and SAGE house style. Instead, these quotations were referenced with parenthetical citations which did not make it clear that they were not the authors’ words.</p>
<p>Choon-Piew Pow and <italic>Theoretical Criminology</italic> apologize to its readers and to the affected authors for this failure to adhere to our usual high standards of publication.</p>
